{
  "texts": [
    "It includes ∼59K English natural language sentences from broadcast conversations, newswires, weblogs, web discussion forums, fiction, and web text.",
    "EnrichmentWhile AMR annotations have been updated throughout time, several approaches have been proposed to enrich the AMRs to cover more semantics and meaning.",
    "As AMR fails to capture time and aspect, Donatelli et al. [25] proposed an annotation scheme to support concepts for time such as past, now, future, and concepts for aspects including stable, ongoing, and complete.",
    "Later, approaches explored automating the enrichment of AMRs.",
    "For example, 𝐴 3 [46], enriches AMRs to better represent numbers, (in)definite articles, quantification determiners, and intentional arguments."
  ]
}